      "content": "a dictionary might actually be worse for memory in python because of the overhead per key-value pair... if the grid is dense i'll just end up with a Memory Limit Exceeded regardless. \n\nis there a way to do it with just a couple of rows at a time to save space? or maybe some trick with how python handles memory so the judge doesn't spike? i just need to see something that actually passes the 64MB limit. show me the code.",
